# Bottega — local / infra-specific instructions (EXAMPLE TEMPLATE)

Copy this file to `CLAUDE.local.md` (which is **gitignored**) and fill in the
values for YOUR environment:

```bash
cp CLAUDE.local.md.example CLAUDE.local.md
```

`CLAUDE.local.md` loads automatically alongside `CLAUDE.md` every session and
holds machine/operator-specific context that should never be committed: dev-box
URLs, deploy layout, manual-test fixtures, and auth tokens. The committed
`CLAUDE.md` stays generic and public; anything specific to how *your* box runs
Bottega goes here instead.

> Using git worktrees / claude-squad? A gitignored `CLAUDE.local.md` only exists
> in the worktree where you created it. This repo's `.githooks/post-checkout`
> copies `CLAUDE.local.md` into each new worktree automatically (alongside
> `.env`), so create it once in your main checkout.

## Development environment

- Where does your instance run? (local only, or a VPS / dev box)
- Public or reverse-proxy URL, if any: `https://<your-domain>` — note whether it
  is real production or a proxy to the same dev server.
- Local URLs: frontend `http://localhost:5173`, backend `http://localhost:3001`.

## Deployment

- How the app is started (e.g. systemd user service `bottega.service` under user
  `<user>`, managed with `systemctl --user`; or a process manager of your choice).
- Any other services it orchestrates via the "switch server" feature.
- Redeploy mechanism — how a push to `main` reaches the server (CI/CD, or a
  manual `git pull` + restart).
- Restart/stop commands and health check for your setup.

## Manual-test fixtures

- A dedicated test project id to use for throwaway manual tasks: `<id>`
  (so you don't pollute real projects — creating a task also creates a git
  worktree and branch on the target repo).

## Auth token for Playwright / MCP testing

- `AUTH_TOKEN` in `.env` is a per-user API key. Note which user it resolves to.
- Seed it into the MCP browser's localStorage to skip the login form:
  ```js
  localStorage.setItem('auth-token', '<AUTH_TOKEN value from .env>');
  ```
- **Never paste the token value into a file checked into git** — keep it in
  `.env` only.

## Worktree workflow (if you use git worktrees / claude-squad)

- Your canonical checkout path, and the rule: edit in the worktree, never in the
  canonical checkout that runs the live service.
- `node_modules` is symlinked from the main checkout by `.githooks/post-checkout`
  — do NOT `pnpm install` inside a worktree (it mutates main's deps); `rm
  node_modules` first if your branch changes dependencies.
